Welcome to Nexi in Austria!

In Austria, we operate from two different locations. Our head office is located in Leobersdorf, close to our capital Vienna and it is easy to reach by train. It is a small but inviting office on the second floor of the building. Our office consists of open spaces, a meeting room and a kitchen where we spend our lunch breaks together.

Our second office is located in Graz, for our colleagues who live in Graz and the surrounding area. There are four offices and a small meeting room.

Welcome to our Zagreb office!

 

In the Croatian capital we operate from our headquarters at Slavonska avenija 1A in so-called Matrix building where we occupy three vast floors. Our premises make a perfect playground: besides pleasant open space offices, there are focus rooms, modular meeting rooms, a spacious kitchen on each floor plus a cozy company library. The central building is an office of more than 300 employees, while we also have a small team of 20 colleagues who work in the card factory situated in the western suburb of Zagreb. Btw, did we tell you we're a pet-friendly workplace? Yep, your four-legged companion will be warmly welcomed here, bring him along!

webparts.innerHtml:
Nexi Italy in numbers

 

+3.755 employees

+6 locations

Revenue €1,966.0 M

With the new way of working in mind, the buildings have been completely redesigned to provide colleagues with a stimulating working environment that encourages collaboration and the exchange of ideas: 60% workspace and 40% co-working space. The building can accommodate up to 1,400 people. The Sempione site employs around 1,200 people.
There are several bookable meeting rooms equipped with video conferencing technology, meeting rooms such as Focus boot and Meeting boot, as well as other reserved spaces for informal and face-to-face meetings. We also have auditoriums and special event rooms. 
Lockers are available for the storage of personal belongings.
On the floors there are spacious break areas (with vending machines with free coffee and water) where you can take breaks and exchange ideas; there are also kitchenettes with microwave ovens for shared meals with colleagues. 
There are directional signs and signage at the entrance and on the floors to help you find your way around the building.  
We are an ESG company and promote alternative mobility: there are special car-sharing spaces in the building and an area for charging scooters and electric bicycles.

What to expect on the first day?

 

We will meet on the first day at the headquarter in Milan - c.so Sempione 55 while colleagues coming from other locations in Italy, we will set-up a Teams meeting.
The invite with all organizational information will arrive at your e-mail address approximately two weeks before your start date.

What to expect in the first weeks?

 

  • An Onboarding Session on your first working day to plug you in
  • A friendly Buddy to help you started
  • An Onboarding Plan to give you structure

  • A supportive environment to make you thrive….

Sweden
Welcome to Nets in Sweden - part of the Nexi Family

…and to our office located in the heart of Gullmarsplan! Situated on the 14th and 15th floors, our workspace offers great views of the beautiful Stockholm skyline, providing an inspiring backdrop for your daily endeavors.

Convenience is key here. In addition to our own lunchroom there is a plethora of restaurants and cafés just a stone's throw away, perfect for grabbing a quick bite or enjoying a leisurely lunch with colleagues. And speaking of lunch breaks, why not take a stroll by the water nearby for a refreshing change of scenery.

We prioritize your well-being with our on-site changing room facility, complete with towel service, making it easy for you to fit in a workout or maybe to freshen up after biking to work (bicycle garage in the building). If you want training buddies, we are a crew meeting every week to exercise together. You are welcome to join us!

Our open-plan offices extend over the 2nd and 5th floors of the building, offering generous space and an inspiring working atmosphere. There is a meeting room on both floors, as well as further retreats for undisturbed telephone calls or smaller meetings.
Both floors are equipped with a modern kitchen where you can grab a cup of coffee or a snack at any time. There is also a cozy "cafeteria" area, which is perfect for breaks, lunch or informal meetings. 
In the immediate vicinity of the office, within walking distance, is the large Glatt shopping center with a variety of shopping opportunities as well as many other restaurants and stores with catering options.
